 https://zoom.us/rec/share/MpT89ozHtOka4-xpo4ftCP2AstUsN8JCb_TYhIVUYOVskcjLgniLgdG_j_zoLhPR.OOseXqBZ5LRijFhT

Summary :

 * Updates : FAPI 1.0​
   PRs supporting additional security features for FAPI 1.0 final have been merged. ​
   Confirmed keycloak passed conformance tests for FAPI 1.0 final.​

 * Updates : FAPI 2.0​
   Review of PR for PAR design document is in progress.​
   https://github.com/keycloak/keycloak-community/pull/255

   Review of PR for RAR design document is in progress.​
   https://github.com/keycloak/keycloak-community/pull/266

   Review of PR for Grant Management API design document is in progress.​
   https://github.com/keycloak/keycloak-community/pull/265

 * Updates : FAPI-CIBA​
   Review of PR supporting OIDC CIBA is still in progress.
   https://github.com/keycloak/keycloak/pull/7679

 * Updates : Common Security Features​
   PR for OIDC Client’s Public Key Management 1st phase has been submitted.​
   https://github.com/keycloak/keycloak/pull/7874

 * Updates : Client Policies​
   PRs revising existing client policies for JSON representation have been merged.​
   https://github.com/keycloak/keycloak/pull/7780

 * Updates : SPA/Native App​
   Review of PR for DPoP design document is in progress.​
   https://github.com/keycloak/keycloak-community/pull/254

 * Updates : PSD2​
   Review of PR for MTLS validation extension design document is in progress.
   https://github.com/keycloak/keycloak-community/pull/267

 * Other Discussion Topics
   - RHSSO 7.5 might be based on keycloak 14.
   - keycloak 14 might include OIDC CIBA and FAPI 1.0 (with Client Policies).
   - keycloak 14 might not include FAPI-CIBA.
   - keycloak 14 might not include new admin console UI.
   - The discussion on what should be included into pre-set profiles is ongoing on keycloak dev-ml.
   - The latest tag version of FAPI conformance suite v4.1.10 does not include FAPI 1.0 final specific part (ex. request object's exp and its expiration data check).

 * Next Web Meeting
   Wed 12 May 2021 11:00 - 12:00 UTC in 1 hour

 